      <li>• <strong>Exfoliate with care:</strong> Gently exfoliate the waxed area 2-3 times a week to keep those pesky ingrown hairs at bay.</li>
      <li>• <strong>Hydrate, hydrate, hydrate:</strong> Moisturize the area daily to keep your skin looking and feeling its best.</li>
      <li>• <strong>Cool it down:</strong> If redness or irritation occurs, a cool compress or aloe vera gel will be your skin's best friend.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-red-700">✗ Don'ts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
      <li>• <strong>Stay away from heat:</strong> Hot showers, hot tubs, saunas, and swimming are a no-go for at least 24 hours after waxing.</li>
      <li>• <strong>Nix the nasties:</strong> Avoid any products that contain alcohol, fragrances, or dyes on the treated area.</li>
      <li>• <strong>Cover up:</strong> Avoid tight clothing and direct sun exposure for at least 24 hours to prevent any irritation.</li>
      <li>• <strong>Resist the urge to pick:</strong> Don't pick or scratch the treated area, as this can lead to infection and scarring.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

